{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Cloud*. Using *JIRA Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-33841].
  {panel}

I mentioned myself in a JIRA ticket, along with several others. I then received an email stating "Jason Birch mentioned you on XXX-123" with a subject including "Jason Birch mentioned you". It is a little confusing to mix the third and second narrative modes.

Technically affects 6.1-OD-03, but that version is not available to tag. Tagging as 6.1-OD-02 in lieu.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Cloud*. Using *JIRA Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-33838].
  {panel}

We are transitioning from another system, and have a lot of data to import using the CSV import. We would like to be able to import the Epic and Sprint fields as part of our stories, which are Greenhopper fields. However, this does not appear to be supported.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Cloud*. Using *JIRA Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-33834].
  {panel}

Currently if you select the sub-task column to be displayed in the issue navigator screen only the Open/Closed status of the sub-task is indicated by either having the sub-task crossed or not.

This improvement request is to have the actual status of the sub-task displayed as well (In progress/Resolved/Closed/Open/Waiting, etc). 

It would be also nice to have the severity of the sub-task to be displayed.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Cloud*. Using *JIRA Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-33833].
  {panel}

It would be nice, if JIRA would display as many transitions as possible directly and just move the ones not fitting on screen to the Workflow-Button. This way UI would optimize for wider and small screens dynamically.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
