  {panel}

{quote}
Since it adds the comment as a LITERAL comment to the issue (with no notation that it's related to a code commit...and thus no way to distinguish it from ACTUAL comments.)  We are curious to know if there is a way to add other variables, such as the file's path, or other things that would help code commits LOOK as such, and not appear to be random comments that disrupt the discourse of issue discussion by being unnecessarily and excessively noisy and, more problematically, ambiguous.
{quote}

